# Customers API

This is a simple API for managing customer data.

## Installation

1. Make sure you have Go installed on your system.
2. Clone this repository to your local machine.
3. Navigate to the project directory.

## Usage

To run the API, use the following steps:

1. Open a terminal window and navigate to the project directory.
2. Run the following command to start the server:

```bash
go run main.go

1. The server will start on port 3000. You can access the API at http://localhost:3000.

Endpoints
The following endpoints are available:
- GET /customers: Get a list of all customers.
- GET /customers/{id}: Get details of a specific customer.
- POST /customers: Add a new customer.
- PATCH /customers/{id}: Update an existing customer.
- DELETE /customers/{id}: Delete an existing customer.

API Information
- API Name: Customers API
- Description: This API allows you to manage customer data.
- Available Endpoints:
    - GET /customers: Get a list of customers.
    - GET /customers/{id}: Get details of a customer.
    - POST /customers: Add a new customer.
    - PATCH /customers/{id}: Update an existing customer.
    - DELETE /customers/{id}: Delete an existing customer.
Please refer to the respective endpoint descriptions for more details on how to use them.

